result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessica Rae Lee was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Take and Drive Vehicle w/o Consent, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(2).
  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jessica Rae vr29Lee in court with attorney Caitlin Hazard Firer.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Rebekkah L.   Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law. 
AS TO COUNT 1:
 The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS, with credit for 268 days time served concurrent with count 2; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS. 

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

AS TO COUNT 2:
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in jail concurrent with count 1., with credit for 268 days time served. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
* Mental Health Evaluation and take all prescribed medications.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
   and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol.  Unless medically assisted treatment.
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Restitution set at $0.00. 
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered with tax intercept.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon she may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended and she may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored.  

The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, and surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b).

Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
